IN THIS INTERVIEW BASIL JOSEPH was only 14 .
 
Director of the movies Kunjiramayanam,Godha and Minnal Murali   | Actor in Jaya Jaya Jaya hai |  Maranamass, Ponman, Sookshmadarshini                                                                 
basil Joseph is An engineer by profession, a film maker by passion.                                                                                                                   #kairalitv #kairalinews 

Basil Joseph is an Indian film director and actor in Malayalam films. He received his secondary education at St. Joseph's English Higher Secondary School in Sultan Bathery, where he demonstrated his versatility as a student by actively participating in sports, choir, and drama.

During his time at the College of Engineering in Trivandrum, Basil  continued to develop his diverse interests through involvement in extracurricular activities and participation in competitions. After graduation, he began a successful career at Infosys, a leading software company.

While working at Infosys, Joseph made his first zero-budget short film, Priyamvadha Katharayano, a quirky love story, and was noticed by  Malayalam Film industry. He was only 22 then.

His passion for cinema led him to quit his job at Infosys and pursue a career as a full-time filmmaker and actor.

Basil Joseph started as an assistant director for Thira in 2013, and his first film as a director was Kunjiramayanam (2015) in 2015.

snippet.description:
Doomed in 59 Seconds: Real Stories from the Flight That Never Landed | Ahmedabad Plane Crash
In just 59 seconds, everything changed. What began as a routine flight filled with excited families, first-time flyers, and last-minute goodbye texts, turned into an unthinkable tragedy. As AI 171 took off, some passengers were heading home, others off to summer vacations â€” none of them knowing it would be their final journey. This video reconstructs the flight moment by moment: from the unusual dip at 14 seconds, to the explosion at 30 seconds. No "landed safely" messages followed. Instead, chaos unfolded on the ground â€” hospitals overwhelmed, families waiting, lives shattered. Survivors speak: one missed the flight by just hours, another saved by traffic, one more who jumped. This is more than a crash; itâ€™s a story of loss, fate, and the fragile seconds that change everything.

snippet.title: GRILLED CHICKEN WINGS | Juicy BBQ Chicken Wings Grilled in Village | Smoky Charcoal Chicken Recipe
snippet.description:
In this video, we prepare delicious grilled chicken wings using a traditional charcoal firewood grill in our village. The chicken wings are marinated with a homemade blend of spices, curd, and a hint of lemon for that perfect tang. Cooked slowly over glowing embers, every bite is juicy, smoky, and full of authentic BBQ flavor.

Watch as we roast the wings to golden perfection on skewers, turning them gently to prevent burning and retain moisture. The smoky aroma, the natural outdoor cooking, and the crispy edges come together to make this one of the best chicken recipes we'll ever try.

id.title: SAYAP AYAM PANGGANG | Sayap Ayam Panggang Lezat di Desa | Resep Ayam Panggang Arang Asap
id.description:
Dalam video ini, kami menyiapkan sayap ayam panggang yang lezat menggunakan panggangan arang kayu bakar tradisional di desa kami. Sayap ayam direndam dengan campuran rempah-rempah, dadih, dan sedikit lemon buatan sendiri untuk rasa asam yang sempurna. Dimasak perlahan di atas bara api yang menyala, setiap gigitannya berair, berasap, dan penuh dengan cita rasa BBQ yang autentik.

Saksikan saat kami memanggang sayap hingga keemasan sempurna di tusuk sate, membaliknya dengan lembut agar tidak gosong dan mempertahankan kelembapan. Aroma berasap, masakan alami di luar ruangan, dan tepian yang renyah berpadu menjadikan ini salah satu resep ayam terbaik yang pernah kami coba.

snippet.description:
Man Escapes Air India Crash by One Flight - He Noticed Something Strange!


A devastating incident involving Air India Flight 171â€”a Boeing 787-8 Dreamlinerâ€”has resulted in numerous fatalities after the aircraft crashed shortly after takeoff from Ahmedabad airport on its way to London. A passenger who had traveled on the same aircraft just two hours earlier, on a Delhi-to-Ahmedabad leg, took to social media to report troubling technical issues. He pointed out that the air conditioning and in-flight entertainment systems were not functioning, sparking serious concerns about the planeâ€™s upkeep and overall safety.

The tragedy has put a renewed spotlight on Air Indiaâ€™s operational practices, with the passengerâ€™s account raising further doubts about the airline's service standards and safety track record. The Boeing 787-8, equipped with Rolls Royce Trent 1000 engines, has previously encountered mechanical challengesâ€”now prompting investigations into potential system failures or deliberate interference. *Crossing India for Free ~ Original by Monkey Magic*
about Day 13 
In this video I hitchhike from New Delhi to Ratlam in a truck, the idea was to go and stand on the Delhi - Mumbai Expressway and go wherever the truck takes me. I wanted to enter the world of truck drivers, how they do what they do. How do they manage to drive for hours and hours, where do they eat? How do they wash? Where do they sleep? How much do they earn? 

This video answers every question from a very humane perspective. 

 *About Crossing India for FREE (K2K)* ğŸ‡®ğŸ‡³
What was the last time you pushed yourself out of your comfort zone? 

This is a super fun reality show series where I have to reach Kanyakumari for Free and if I spend some money on the road then I have to earn that money back by doing random jobs on the road itself. 
30 days to reach Kanyakumari 
30 days of daily videos documenting this journey

snippet.title: Young Air India Crew Member From Manipur Killed in Flight AI171 Crash
snippet.description:
Just hours before boarding Air India Flight AI171 to London, 21-year-old Nganthoi Sharma from Manipur made a final call to her sister. Minutes after takeoff, the aircraft crashed near Ahmedabad, leaving her family in shock and mourning. As DNA identification continues, her loved ones remember a vibrant young woman who followed her dreams into the skiesâ€”only to be lost too soon.

id.title: Awak Muda Air India Asal Manipur Tewas dalam Kecelakaan Pesawat AI171
id.description:
Beberapa jam sebelum menaiki Pesawat Air India AI171 menuju London, Nganthoi Sharma yang berusia 21 tahun dari Manipur menelepon saudara perempuannya untuk terakhir kalinya. en.title: Young Air India Crew Member From Manipur Killed in Flight AI171 Crash
en.description:
Just hours before boarding Air India Flight AI171 to London, 21-year-old Nganthoi Sharma from Manipur made a final call to her sister. Minutes after takeoff, the aircraft crashed near Ahmedabad, leaving her family in shock and mourning. As DNA identification continues, her loved ones remember a vibrant young woman who followed her dreams into the skiesâ€”only to be lost too soon.

A failed rebellion, the death of a friend, and a secret betrayal. We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Sachin Shroff / Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Jheel Mehta / Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani / Khushi Mali as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder Suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal / Monaz Mevawalla as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi 
Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi
Kush Shah / Dharmit Shah as Gulabkumar Hansraj Hathi (Goli)
Shyam Pathak as Popatlal Pandey
Sharad Sankla as Abdul
Azhar Shaikh as Pinku 
Ghanshyam Nayak / Kiran Bhatt as Nattu Kaka
Tanmay Vekaria as Bagha
Navina Wadekar / Monika Bhadoriya as Bawri

The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalalâ€™s Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

Click here to watch full episodes of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLSXTaG1fT0cTXtajBo1G2UEa_wE8BVSU7

Ghatak :-
Kashi Nath is a kind-hearted wrestler and the dutiful adopted son of Shambhu Nath, living in Banaras. Shambhu Nath, who was a freedom fighter awarded with the Tambra Patra, is an honourable and respectable man in town. Kashi, along with Shambhu, comes to Mumbai for medical treatment for Shambhu and stays with his brother, Shiv Nath. Kashi meets Gauri in the colony and starts liking her. He learns that the colony is being terrorized by the tyrannical gangster, Katya, along with his six brothers. Before Kashi's arrival, a resident named Sachdev tried to initiate a revolt against Katya, but got ruthlessly killed by him, thereby making Malti, Sachdev's wife, go mad. Katya and his brothers become enemies with Kashi when he beats up their goons in the process of roughing up Malti.

He learns that the colony is being terrorized by the tyrannical gangster, Katya, along with his six brothers. Before Kashi's arrival, a resident named Sachdev tried to initiate a revolt against Katya, but got ruthlessly killed by him, thereby making Malti, Sachdev's wife, go mad. Katya and his brothers become enemies with Kashi when he beats up their goons in the process of roughing up Malti.

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu)
